================================================================================
Exercise 1: Generate Test Cases for Team & Support Portal
================================================================================

Core Prompt:
Generate comprehensive test cases for this repository’s **Team & Support Portal**:
a React + TypeScript (Vite) front end with hash routes (`#/team`, `#/support`) and a
Flask JWT API. Cover **team dashboard** flows (projects, tasks, project health status,
members, notifications/activity feed, quick actions and modals) and **customer support**
flows (ticket list/create, role-based access for `customer` / `agent` / `admin`,
status transitions, admin metrics and agent assignment, SLA-related behavior where
exposed, comments and attachments if applicable). Include **authentication** (register,
login, protected routes, invalid/expired token handling). Include positive scenarios,
negative scenarios, edge cases (empty project list, no tasks, rate limits on ticket
creation), and security scenarios (JWT misuse, input sanitization on ticket subject/
description and comments, IDOR or cross-user ticket access, SQL injection / XSS in
user-supplied fields, support RBAC enforcement).


Expected Deliverables:
 - 30+ test cases across all categories
 - Positive test cases (happy paths: login → team dashboard load; create/update task;
   project status change; support ticket lifecycle for each relevant role)
 - Negative test cases (API/UI errors, invalid transitions, validation failures,
   unauthorized access without login or wrong support role)
 - Edge cases (concurrent edits, pagination on ticket list, large descriptions within
   limits, missing optional fields)
 - Security test cases (authZ by role, token tampering, injection payloads in text
   fields, safe handling of uploads if present)
 - Automated test scripts aligned with this repo: **Playwright** E2E under `tests/`
   (and optionally Flask **pytest** for critical API-only paths if you document how
   to run them)
 - Test data generation strategy (seed users, demo accounts from README, factories
   for projects/tasks/tickets)


Acceptance Criteria:
 - All critical **#/team** and **#/support** user journeys covered for each role that
   the UI exposes
 - JWT-protected API behavior and support **RBAC** validated in tests or documented
   manual checks
 - Error handling and validation (forms, HTTP 4xx) explicitly tested
 - Test scripts executable in this project (`npm test` / documented commands) and
   passing where automation is in scope
